---
description: Forge runtime, adapter and local reference checkout rules
globs:
  - "engine/**"
  - ".reference/**"
  - "archive/prototypes/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Treat `.reference/` as read-only local reference: never commit, import, patch, or package it.
- Route production Forge integration through Aureline adapters, runtime manifests, and materialization tooling.
- Pin runtime commit/version/checksum and assert compatibility; fail closed on drift.
- Run fixture tests and a real no-model runtime smoke when an integration seam changes.
- Forge is a third-party AGPL-3.0 engine; Aureline's MIT license does not cover Forge source.
- Treat archived prototypes as evidence only; do not import or copy them wholesale into production.
